# Production hosting — MCP-first

When the task touches **production auth**, **email**, **DNS**, **env vars**, **deploys**, or **go-live** for brisbaneservers.com:

1. **Do it yourself** via MCP or documented APIs before asking the user to click dashboards.
2. **Read first:** `docs/operations/HOSTING_MCP_WORKSPACE.md`, `docs/operations/PRODUCTION_GO_LIVE_STATUS.md`.

## MCP servers (`.cursor/mcp.json`)

| Server | Use for |
|--------|---------|
| `cloudflare-api` | Pages env, DNS, Email Routing (`execute` tool) |
| `render` | Service env, deploys, logs (requires `RENDER_AUTH_HEADER` in user env) |

If Render MCP tools are unavailable, use **Render REST API** with `$env:RENDER_API_KEY` (User env). Service id: `srv-d8ae7qbbc2fs73fv227g`.

## Auth email (Resend)

- **Do not** leave `AUTH_EMAIL_FROM` on `onboarding@resend.dev` in production (403 for non-test recipients).
- Verified sending domain in DNS: **`mail.brisbaneservers.com`** (Resend DKIM/SPF already in Cloudflare).
- Production `AUTH_EMAIL_FROM`: `Brisbane Servers <support@mail.brisbaneservers.com>`
- After changing Render env vars, **trigger a redeploy** and test send (Resend API or register flow).
- Target long-term From: `support@brisbaneservers.com` after root domain is verified in Resend (add root DKIM via Cloudflare MCP).

## Google OAuth

- Check `GET /api/auth/oauth/status` on the live API.
- Client ID (production): `1040878189962-o0que80vsplu0vghos3ogdgjdakpvdda.apps.googleusercontent.com`
- Redirect URI on Render: `https://brisbane-servers-api.onrender.com/api/auth/oauth/google/callback` (must match Google Console **Authorized redirect URIs**).
- Set secret via `.\website-brisbaneservers.com\scripts\configure-google-oauth.ps1` (updates Render + user env).
- Cursor Google Cloud MCP uses same env vars; add `cursor://anysphere.cursor-mcp/oauth/callback` in Google Console if using BigQuery MCP.

## After infra changes

- Run `npm run verify:production` from `website-brisbaneservers.com`.
- Update `docs/operations/PRODUCTION_GO_LIVE_STATUS.md` with date and what changed.
- Never print secrets (`CRON_SECRET`, API keys, generated passwords) in chat.
